text: Cnephasia heringi is a species of moth of the family Tortricidae. It is found in Bulgaria, Greece, North Macedonia, Russia and Turkey.Fauna Europaea The length of the forewings is 6.6–8.3 mm for males and 8–9.2 mm for females.Zlatkov, B. (2013): Remarks on Tortricidae species with unknown and little known females. — Nota lepidopterologica 36 (2): 191–197 Adults have been recorded on wing in May. ==References== Category:Moths described in 1958 Category:Cnephasia Category:Moths of Turkey Category:Moths of Russia Category:Moths of Europe Category:Taxa named by Józef Razowski
title: Cnephasia heringi
